===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|boy}}, {{m|enm|boye||servant, commoner, knave, boy}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|*bōia||boy}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*bōjô||younger brother, young male relation}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*bō-||brother, close male relation}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*bʰā-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*bʰāt-||father, elder brother, brother}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{m|sco|boy||boy}}, {{etyl|frs|-}} {{m|frs|boi||boy, young gentleman}}, {{etyl|fy|-}} {{m|fy|boai||boy}}, {{etyl|dum|-}} {{m|dum|boi}}, {{m|dum|booi||boy}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{m|nds|Boi||boy}}, and probably to the {{etyl|ang|-}} proper name ''Bōia''. Also related to {{etyl|vls|-}} {{m|vls|boe||brother}}, {{etyl|no|-}} dialectal {{m|no|boa||brother}}, English ''[[bub#Etymology_3|bub]]'', {{etyl|nl|-}} {{m|nl|boef||rogue, knave}}, {{etyl|de|-}} dialectal {{m|de|Bube||boy, lad, knave}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{m|is|bófi||rogue, crook, bandit, knave}}. See also {{l/en|bully}}.

